00:06:45.360 --> 00:06:51.280
next binding site. The other thing that was really quite shocking to us is we thought, okay, when it

00:06:51.280 --> 00:06:56.560
binds, we thought it's somewhat more stable, and it's really not. And you see this in the lower

00:06:56.560 --> 00:07:02.320
right, so the stable residence time, I mean, first of all, the majority of molecules upper right

00:07:03.200 --> 00:07:08.640
binds only less than one second, so that's the browsing kind of movement, but then even the

00:07:08.640 --> 00:07:15.200
